data.content:
Yes — the cast will throw `InvalidCastException` on failure instead of a clean test failure. Use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType` (MSTest) to verify the type, then cast:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();
    var result = factory.Create("email");

    Assert.IsInstanceOfType(result, typeof(EmailHandler));
    var handler = (EmailHandler)result;
    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

Or with the generic overload (MSTest v2.2.8+), which also returns the typed instance:

```csharp
var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(result);
Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
```

The generic version is the cleanest — it asserts the type **and** gives you the cast in one call.
